No vote.

This whole article is very lukewarm to me. The description was good, but footnotes 1-4 really drag on and add very little. The interview was bland and really wooden in some spots (footnote 5 is bad, and feels more like it's talking down to the reader). The last addendum doesn't do anything for me and is a really out of place student debt joke. This is a genially interesting concept that is brought down by quite a few things.







